msContents.summary: Contains the incomplete text of Isidore's Etymologies (begins in the middle of chapter eight of book three).

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 2 columns of 39 lines (dimensions of written space: 205 x 125 mm); writing begins below the top line; all lines have double prickings; framed ruled in lead with double inner and outer vertical bounding lines; headings written in alternating blue and red letters throughout; minor marginalia with manicules.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written by multiple scribes in a Gothic hand; English cursive hand appears in some places.

decoDesc.decoNote: Decorated with blue and red initials, with pen flourishings throughout. Two consanguinity charts on leaves 74v and 75r.

origin.p: Written in England, probably Oxford, 13th century; 13th century

history.provenance: Given by Wylton to Johannes Wylmyn; also formerly owned by 12th Earl of Kinnoull (bookplate); W.T. Smedley. Purchased as part of the Smedley Collection in 1924 by Henry Clay Folger.
